                    name="Text Container">
                    <item_0
                        jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                        sling:resourceType="core/franklin/components/block/v1/block/item"
                        model="text-container-text"
                        modelFields="[text]"
                        name="Text Container Text"
                        text="&lt;p>Findings from real-world evidence studies like IBD-PODCAST help drive AbbVie's innovative, three-pronged research and development strategy. These new approaches seek to address unmet patient needs:&lt;/p>&lt;p>&lt;ol> &lt;li>&lt;strong>Combination treatments:&lt;/strong>  AbbVie is exploring whether using multiple medications together works better than using them alone. These combinations can help target different parts of the disease process. AbbVie has already started a clinical trial in patients with Crohn's disease and plans to test similar approaches for other immune system disorders.&lt;/li> &lt;li>&lt;strong>New ways medications work:&lt;/strong>  AbbVie is developing medications that work through entirely new biological pathways. These therapies might be used alone or in combination with other treatments, in the hopes of helping to make a long-term impact on patients' lives.&lt;/li> &lt;li>&lt;strong>Personalized approach:&lt;/strong>  AbbVie is advancing precision medicine approaches to match the right treatment with the right patient. Teams look at patient profiles at a molecular level and at a clinical level. This can help to identify better options for patients who aren't responding to current treatments.&lt;/li> &lt;/ol>&lt;/p>&lt;p>&quot;In research and development, we are challenging ourselves to continue to raise the standard of care with therapies that don't just address symptoms, but that can help resolve and potentially cure underlying disease pathology,&quot; said Kori Wallace, vice president and therapeutic area head of immunology at AbbVie.&lt;/p>"/>
                </block_15>
                <block_16
                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                    sling:resourceType="core/franklin/components/block/v1/block"
                    blockId="\0"
                    classes_customDynamicClass="h5-size,width-large"
