                        text="&lt;p>&lt;strong>References:&lt;/strong>&lt;/p>&lt;p>&lt;ol> &lt;li>D'Amico F, Gomollón F, Bamias G, Magro F, Targownik L, Leitner C, Heatta-Speicher T, Michelena N, Kolterer S, Lapthorn J, Kauffman L, Dignass A; IBD PODCAST investigators. Proportion of inflammatory bowel diseases patients with suboptimal disease control in daily clinical practice-Real-world evidence from the inflammatory bowel diseases-podcast study. United European Gastroenterol J. 2024 Jul;12(6):705-716. doi: 10.1002/ueg2.12572. Epub 2024 May 11.&lt;/li> &lt;li>Dignass A, Magro F, D'Amico F, Bamias G, Caprioli FA, Franchimont D, Hart A, Koch R, Koutroubakis I, Siffledeen J, Toruner M, Leitner C, Heatta-Speicher T, Michelena N, Tornatore V, Gemignani L, Lapthorn J, Kauffman L, Gomollón F; IBD‐PODCAST Investigators. Disease Monitoring in Inflammatory Bowel Disease Daily Clinical Practice and Impact on Treatment Decision Making: Real World Evidence From the Inflammatory Bowel Disease-PODCAST Study. United European Gastroenterol J. 2025 Dec;13(10):1984-1998. doi: 10.1002/ueg2.70117. Epub 2025 Oct 13.&lt;/li> &lt;li>&lt;a href=&quot;https://worldibdday.org/about-us&quot;>https://worldibdday.org/about-us&lt;/a>&lt;/li> &lt;/ol>&lt;/p>&lt;p>&lt;strong>Media inquiries:&lt;/strong>&lt;/p>&lt;p>&lt;a href=&quot;mailto:abbviemediarelations@abbvie.com&quot;>abbviemediarelations@abbvie.com&lt;/a>&lt;/p>"/>
